6 (B) improve soils, water, and resiliency of the working landscape in
7 the face of climate change; and
8 (C) improve access to healthy local foods for all Vermonters.
9 (2) As part of the charge of the Vermont Farm-to-Plate Investment
10 Program, the Vermont Sustainable Jobs Fund was tasked with creating a
11 strategic plan for agricultural and food system development.
12 (3) The Vermont Sustainable Jobs Fund issued the Vermont Agriculture
13 and Food System Strategic Plan 2021 to 2030 (Strategic Plan) in 2020 to,
14 among other charges, stabilize and revitalize Vermont’s agricultural industry
15 and increase Vermont farm and food system resilience and security.
16 (4) With the information gathered from development of the Strategic
17 Plan, the Vermont Sustainable Jobs Fund is required to identify methods and
18 the funding necessary to strengthen the links among producers, processors, and
19 markets, including:
20 (A) supporting the work of the Working Lands Enterprise Board to
21 strategically invest in farm and food businesses;
